				\begin{document}$$C\frac{{\rm{d}}T}{{\rm{d}}t}={F}_{\mathrm{SW}}-D-L{E}_{{\rm{S}}}={F}_{\mathrm{SW}}-\alpha (T-\bar{{T}_{{\rm{D}}}})-\frac{L{\rho }_{{\rm{a}}}{M}_{{\rm{S}}}}{{r}_{{\rm{S}}}}[{q}_{\mathrm{sat}}(T)-\bar{q}]$$\end{document}CdTdt=FSW−D−LES=FSW−α(T−TD¯)−LρaMSrS[qsat(T)−q¯]where C is the effective heat capacity of the soil layer, FSW is the net surface shortwave radiation, D is the sum of net longwave radiation and the ground and sensible heat fluxes (that is, the ‘dry’ energetic response), ES is evaporation from soils and L is the enthalpy of vapourization of water. Following ref. 65, D is parameterized as a function of the dewpoint depression (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
